From: amb43790@uxa.cso.uiuc.edu (Tony Brummett)
Subject: SLIP question
Date: 26 Aug 1993 16:12:57 GMT

I'm trying to connect the 2 computers in our room with a TCP/IP network so
we can login and NFS mount stuff between our machines. What I've tried doing
is connecting them together with a serial cable and starting a SLIP
connection on both of them. 

The ifconfig line for my computer is
  ifconfig sl0 100.100.100.2 pointopoint 100.100.100.3
and my roommate's is
  ifconfig sl0 100.100.100.3 pointopoint 100.100.100.2
ifconfig reports that the sl0 device is (UP POINTOPOINT RUNNING) on both ends.

I then start dip on my roommate's computer to set things up and get no errors.
When I start dip on my machine, it immediately prints 'wombat: Error 0' and
exits (wombat.local.net is my machine and weasel.local.net is my roommate's)

If I try 'ping wombat.local.net' from weasel, it sits there and (apparently)
tries pinging, so I believe weasel is set up OK.

Finally my questions... Will this setup work at all? and why won't dip start
up on wombat?

Thanks in advance...

