From: imp@boulder.parcplace.com (Warner Losh)
Subject: Re: Why not create/use auto VESA SVGA X11 drivers? (Possible FAQ entry?)
Date: Thu, 26 Aug 1993 15:50:41 GMT

In article <25giuj$t0j@master.cs.rose-hulman.edu>
mgrstk@NeXTwork.Rose-Hulman.Edu (Steve King) writes: 
>Q: So, does a user with a vesa bus have a problem if he wants to use linux?

No.  I have (had) a VESA system with a UltraStor 34F and a Tsung Labs
ET4000 on the LocalBus.  Both of these cards were supported and worked
quite well with Linux.  The 34F had to be jumpered to a new I/O
address to install SLS, but the ET4000 worked fine out of the box.

I know of several people who are happily running Linux on LocalBus
machines.

